  "body": "### Description\n\nCurrently, there is no way just by looking the generated manifests, to know that the deployed application will attempt at runtime to read a specific `Secret` or `ConfigMap`.\r\n\r\nIn many cases it would be nice to have that info, as it could avoid rbac misconfigurations and help external tools (e.g. openshift, backstage consoles to visualize the dependency).\n\n### Implementation ideas\n\nOne or more Quarkus specific annotations would be enough to express the relation.",
